Bonnie B. CANTRELL, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Robert H. FINCH, Secretary of Health, Education and Welfare, DefendantAppellee. No. 30203

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 16, 1970. George C. Longshore, Cooper, Mitch & Crawford, Birmingham, Ala., for plaintiff-appellant. William D. Ruckelshaus, Asst. Atty. Gen., Wayman G. Sherrer, U. S. Atty., Morton Hollander, Robert M. Feinson, Attys., Dept, of Justice, Washington, D. C., for defendant-appellee.

Before BELL, AINSWORTH and GODBOLD, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5th Cir.; See Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York, et al., 5th Cir., 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.1

. See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 430 F.2d 966 (5th Cir. 1970).
